# React Project Rules

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer functional components with hooks over class components
- Use named exports, not default exports
- Keep components under 200 lines; extract subcomponents when needed

## Architecture
- Follow the feature-based directory structure under src/features/
- Use React Query for server state management
- Use Zustand for client state management
- API calls go in src/api/ with typed response schemas

## Testing
- Write unit tests for all utility functions
- Write integration tests for API hooks
- Use React Testing Library, not Enzyme
- Minimum 80% coverage on new code

## Security
- Always sanitize user input before rendering
- Use DOMPurify for any HTML content
- Never store secrets in client-side code
- Use environment variables for API endpoints
